text:
Clonmel is an unincorporated community in Illinois Township, Sedgwick County, Kansas United States.
History.
Clonmel was a train station on the Kansas City, Mexico and Orient Railway.
The first post office in Clonmel opened in 1905. It closed in 1938. It was named after Clonmel in Ireland.
